d by the Lense--Thiring effect, which has never\nbeen modeled and solved for so far, but can be estimated to $\\approx$ 7\\%. It\nis thus possible to get a good estimate of the solar quadrupole\nmoment:$1.66\\times10^{-7}$$\\leq$$J_2$$\\leq$$2.32\\times10^{-7}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 14 Aug 2022 05:26:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-16"}
