{"id":"2208.10363","submitter":"Wei Zhu","authors":"Wei Zhu and Rong Wang","title":"Looking for the Signals of the Missing Baryons in the Extragalactic\n  Background Light","comments":"11 pages and 2 figures. A modified version and accepted for\n  publication in In.J.Mod.Phys.A","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1142/S0217751X23500136","report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph.CO astro-ph.HE","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  The missing baryons in the universe are assumed to be hidden in the whole\nspace as a warm-hot intergalactic medium (WHIM). Finding them is one of the\nimportant subjects in modern cosmology. In this paper, we point out that the\nvery high energy electron/positron rays may light up the WHIM due to the\nanomalous bremsstrahlung according to an improved Bethe-Heitler formula. The\nresulting excess of the extragalactic background light (EBL) can be observed by\nthe direct measurement method. A possible explanation on the difference between\nthe direct and indirect measurements of EBL is also proposed. Thus, we find a\nnew window to probe the WHIM properties via the EBL.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 14 Aug 2022 08:03:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 20 Jan 2023 20:45:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-19"}
